               <head>Insha collection, fragment</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008116463 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064914 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100074" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4530-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled fragment from a collection of official letters and orders (ʿarz̤ah dāsht, parvānajāt, shuqqajāt, etc.), several of which touch on a common subject, that of Awadh's relations with the Afghan rulers of the Rohelkhand region (UP), involving Afghan depredation in Farrukhabad, and a certain Qudrat ʿAlī Khān at Lucknow and the military build up of his forces at Bholi and Faizullahnagar, etc. </p>
                        <p>Notes on flyleave: 1) <q>Fragment of a Collection of Reports by a Lakhnau Amil about 1161-1162 H - Sent by Dirga Parshad Wakil, October 18 1877</q>; 2) <q>Removed from a volume of Lithographs, mainly Urdu, belonging to the Irvine Collection</q> (in pencil) 
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning and end, thus not dated </p>
                        <p>Partially foliated in Persian (folios 9-35): estimated 26 folios approximately </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="eng">Persian and English </textLang>
                  </msItem>
